questiontext.text:
You are playing a game which involves moving a token in a clockwise direction around a circular board.  An image of this board is shown below:


Given the starting position of the token (as a capital letter), and the number of steps to take (clockwise) you need to work out what the ending position of the token will be (expressed as a capital letter).  For example, if the token starts at position 'C' and moves two steps, then it will end at position 'E'.  Likewise, if the token starts at position 'X' and moves 5 steps, it will end at position 'C'. 

Write a C program that prompts the user to enter the letter corresponding to where the token starts (you can assume they will enter a capital letter).  The program should then prompt the user to enter the number of steps that the token should move.  Finally, the program should calculate and display the position where the token will end (this should be displayed as a capital letter).  A stylized arrow is also shown in the output and includes the number of steps.

expected.text: Enter letter: Enter steps: C -- 2 --> E
Enter letter: Enter steps: X -- 5 --> C
Enter letter: Enter steps: R -- 32 --> X
Enter letter: Enter steps: N -- 12 --> Z
Enter letter: Enter steps: Q -- 123 --> J
Enter letter: Enter steps: B -- 222 --> P
Enter letter: Enter steps: Y -- 2 --> A
Enter letter: Enter steps: G -- 321 --> P
Enter letter: Enter steps: E -- 26 --> E
Enter letter: Enter steps: E -- 27 --> F
